{"declarations":[{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Async/Timer.html#Std.Async.Interval.stop\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Async</span>.<span class=\"name\">Interval</span>.<span class=\"name\">stop</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">i</span> : <a href=\"./Std/Async/Timer.html#Std.Async.Interval\">Interval</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/System/IO.html#IO\">IO</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Unit\">Unit</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If:\n- `i` is still running this stops `i` without completing any remaining `Async` computations that were created\n  through `tick`. Note that if another `Async` computation is binding on any of these it will hang\n  forever without further intervention.\n- `i` is not yet or not anymore running this is a no-op.\n","docLink":"./Std/Async/Timer.html#Std.Async.Interval.stop","kind":"def","line":155,"name":"Std.Async.Interval.stop","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Std/Async/Timer.lean#L155-L164"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Async/Timer.html#Std.Async.Interval.reset\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Async</span>.<span class=\"name\">Interval</span>.<span class=\"name\">reset</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">i</span> : <a href=\"./Std/Async/Timer.html#Std.Async.Interval\">Interval</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/System/IO.html#IO\">IO</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Unit\">Unit</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If:\n- `Interval.tick` was called on `i` before the timer restarts counting from now and the next tick\n   happens in `duration`.\n- `i` is not yet or not anymore running this is a no-op.\n","docLink":"./Std/Async/Timer.html#Std.Async.Interval.reset","kind":"def","line":145,"name":"Std.Async.Interval.reset","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Std/Async/Timer.lean#L145-L153"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Async/Timer.html#Std.Async.Interval.tick\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Async</span>.<span class=\"name\">Interval</span>.<span class=\"name\">tick</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">i</span> : <a href=\"./Std/Async/Timer.html#Std.Async.Interval\">Interval</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Std/Async/Basic.html#Std.Async.Async\">Async</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Unit\">Unit</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If:\n- `i` is not yet running start it and return an `Async` computation that completes right away as the 0th\n  multiple of `duration` has elapsed.\n- `i` is already running and:\n  - the tick from the last call of `i` has not yet finished return the same `Async` computation as the last\n    call\n  - the tick from the last call of `i` has finished return a new `Async` computation that waits for the\n    closest next tick from the time of calling this function.\n- `i` is not running anymore this is a no-op.\n","docLink":"./Std/Async/Timer.html#Std.Async.Interval.tick","kind":"def","line":130,"name":"Std.Async.Interval.tick","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Std/Async/Timer.lean#L130-L143"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Async/Timer.html#Std.Async.Interval.mk\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Async</span>.<span class=\"name\">Interval</span>.<span class=\"name\">mk</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">duration</span> : <a href=\"./Std/Time/Time/Unit/Millisecond.html#Std.Time.Millisecond.Offset\">Time.Millisecond.Offset</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Tactics.html#autoParam\">autoParam</a> (<span class=\"fn\">0</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LT.lt\">&lt;</a> <span class=\"fn\">duration</span>) <a href=\"./Std/Async/Timer.html#Std.Async.Interval.mk\">mk._auto_1</a></span> → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/System/IO.html#IO\">IO</a> <a href=\"./Std/Async/Timer.html#Std.Async.Interval\">Interval</a></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Setup up an `Interval` that waits for `duration` milliseconds.\nThis function only initializes but does not yet start the timer.\n","docLink":"./Std/Async/Timer.html#Std.Async.Interval.mk","kind":"def","line":121,"name":"Std.Async.Interval.mk","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Std/Async/Timer.lean#L121-L128"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Async/Timer.html#Std.Async.Interval.native\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Async</span>.<span class=\"name\">Interval</span>.<span class=\"name\">native</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Std/Async/Timer.html#Std.Async.Interval\">Interval</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Std/Internal/UV/Timer.html#Std.Internal.UV.Timer\">Internal.UV.Timer</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Std/Async/Timer.html#Std.Async.Interval.native","kind":"def","line":117,"name":"Std.Async.Interval.native","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Std/Async/Timer.lean#L117-L117"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">structure</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Async/Timer.html#Std.Async.Interval\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Async</span>.<span class=\"name\">Interval</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"`Interval` can be used to repeatedly wait for some duration like a clock.\nThe underlying timer has millisecond resolution.\n","docLink":"./Std/Async/Timer.html#Std.Async.Interval","kind":"structure","line":111,"name":"Std.Async.Interval","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Std/Async/Timer.lean#L111-L117"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Async/Timer.html#Std.Async.Selector.sleep\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Async</span>.<span class=\"name\">Selector</span>.<span class=\"name\">sleep</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">duration</span> : <a href=\"./Std/Time/Time/Unit/Millisecond.html#Std.Time.Millisecond.Offset\">Time.Millisecond.Offset</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Std/Async/Basic.html#Std.Async.Async\">Async</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Std/Async/Select.html#Std.Async.Selector\">Selector</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Unit\">Unit</a>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Return a `Selector` that completes after `duration`.\n","docLink":"./Std/Async/Timer.html#Std.Async.Selector.sleep","kind":"def","line":104,"name":"Std.Async.Selector.sleep","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Std/Async/Timer.lean#L104-L109"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Async/Timer.html#Std.Async.sleep\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Async</span>.<span class=\"name\">sleep</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">duration</span> : <a href=\"./Std/Time/Time/Unit/Millisecond.html#Std.Time.Millisecond.Offset\">Time.Millisecond.Offset</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Std/Async/Basic.html#Std.Async.Async\">Async</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Unit\">Unit</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Return an `Async` computation that completes after `duration`.\n","docLink":"./Std/Async/Timer.html#Std.Async.sleep","kind":"def","line":97,"name":"Std.Async.sleep","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Std/Async/Timer.lean#L97-L102"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Async/Timer.html#Std.Async.Sleep.selector\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Async</span>.<span class=\"name\">Sleep</span>.<span class=\"name\">selector</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">s</span> : <a href=\"./Std/Async/Timer.html#Std.Async.Sleep\">Sleep</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Std/Async/Select.html#Std.Async.Selector\">Selector</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Unit\">Unit</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Create a `Selector` that resolves once `s` has finished. `s` only starts when it runs inside of a Selectable.\n","docLink":"./Std/Async/Timer.html#Std.Async.Sleep.selector","kind":"def","line":69,"name":"Std.Async.Sleep.selector","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Std/Async/Timer.lean#L69-L93"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Async/Timer.html#Std.Async.Sleep.stop\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Async</span>.<span class=\"name\">Sleep</span>.<span class=\"name\">stop</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">s</span> : <a href=\"./Std/Async/Timer.html#Std.Async.Sleep\">Sleep</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/System/IO.html#IO\">IO</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Unit\">Unit</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If:\n- `s` is still running this stops `s` without completing any remaining `Async` computations that were created\n  through `wait`. Note that if another `Async` computation is binding on any of these it will hang\n  forever without further intervention.\n- `s` is not yet or not anymore running this is a no-op.\n","docLink":"./Std/Async/Timer.html#Std.Async.Sleep.stop","kind":"def","line":58,"name":"Std.Async.Sleep.stop","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Std/Async/Timer.lean#L58-L67"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Async/Timer.html#Std.Async.Sleep.reset\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Async</span>.<span class=\"name\">Sleep</span>.<span class=\"name\">reset</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">s</span> : <a href=\"./Std/Async/Timer.html#Std.Async.Sleep\">Sleep</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Std/Async/Basic.html#Std.Async.Async\">Async</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Unit\">Unit</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If:\n- `s` is still running the timer restarts counting from now and completes after `duration`\n  milliseconds.\n- `s` is not yet or not anymore running this is a no-op.\n","docLink":"./Std/Async/Timer.html#Std.Async.Sleep.reset","kind":"def","line":48,"name":"Std.Async.Sleep.reset","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Std/Async/Timer.lean#L48-L56"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Async/Timer.html#Std.Async.Sleep.wait\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Async</span>.<span class=\"name\">Sleep</span>.<span class=\"name\">wait</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">s</span> : <a href=\"./Std/Async/Timer.html#Std.Async.Sleep\">Sleep</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Std/Async/Basic.html#Std.Async.Async\">Async</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Unit\">Unit</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If:\n- `s` is not yet running start it and return an `Async` computation that will complete once the previously\n   configured `duration` has elapsed.\n- `s` is already or not anymore running return the same `Async` computation as the first call to `wait`.\n","docLink":"./Std/Async/Timer.html#Std.Async.Sleep.wait","kind":"def","line":38,"name":"Std.Async.Sleep.wait","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Std/Async/Timer.lean#L38-L46"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Async/Timer.html#Std.Async.Sleep.mk\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Async</span>.<span class=\"name\">Sleep</span>.<span class=\"name\">mk</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">duration</span> : <a href=\"./Std/Time/Time/Unit/Millisecond.html#Std.Time.Millisecond.Offset\">Time.Millisecond.Offset</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Std/Async/Basic.html#Std.Async.Async\">Async</a> <a href=\"./Std/Async/Timer.html#Std.Async.Sleep\">Sleep</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Set up a `Sleep` that waits for `duration` milliseconds.\nThis function only initializes but does not yet start the timer.\n","docLink":"./Std/Async/Timer.html#Std.Async.Sleep.mk","kind":"def","line":29,"name":"Std.Async.Sleep.mk","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Std/Async/Timer.lean#L29-L36"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Async/Timer.html#Std.Async.Sleep.native\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Async</span>.<span class=\"name\">Sleep</span>.<span class=\"name\">native</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Std/Async/Timer.html#Std.Async.Sleep\">Sleep</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Std/Internal/UV/Timer.html#Std.Internal.UV.Timer\">Internal.UV.Timer</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Std/Async/Timer.html#Std.Async.Sleep.native","kind":"def","line":25,"name":"Std.Async.Sleep.native","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Std/Async/Timer.lean#L25-L25"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">structure</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Async/Timer.html#Std.Async.Sleep\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Async</span>.<span class=\"name\">Sleep</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"`Sleep` can be used to sleep for some duration once.\nThe underlying timer has millisecond resolution.\n","docLink":"./Std/Async/Timer.html#Std.Async.Sleep","kind":"structure","line":19,"name":"Std.Async.Sleep","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Std/Async/Timer.lean#L19-L25"}}],"imports":["Std.Async.Select","Std.Internal.UV.Timer","Std.Time"],"instances":[],"name":"Std.Async.Timer"}